Unicode has released the data for Emoji 11.0, which includes 157 new emoji. The Emoji 11.0 set is fixed and final, and includes the data needed for vendors to begin working on their emoji fonts and code ahead of the release – scheduled for June 2018. The new emoji typically start showing up on mobile phones in August or September. Additions include the man and woman emoji now having various hair styles – like red hair or curly hair – and the new superheros and supervillains featuring genders and skin tones. The new emoji are listed in Emoji Recently Added v11.0, with sample images.